    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I think it can usefull to test if a transaction already started and not commited or rolled back.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
function update() {
    $db = WebD::Db::getInstance();
    $db-&gt;beginTransaction();
    try {
        $db-&gt;update( ... );
        // if this changed all linked data must change too
        updateAnother();
        $db-&gt;commit();
    } catch (Exception $e) {
        $db-&gt;rollBack();
        throw $e;
    }
}

function updateAnother() {
    $db = WebD::Db::getInstance();
    if ($db-&gt;transactionStarted()) {
        $db-&gt;update( [1] );
        $db-&gt;update( [2] );
    } else {
        $db-&gt;beginTransaction();
        try {
            $db-&gt;update( [1] );
            $db-&gt;update( [2] );
            $db-&gt;commit();
        } catch (Exception $e) {
            $db-&gt;rollBack();
            throw $e;
        }
    }
}

</code></pre>

